persepolis ( old persian : pārśa,the greeks and the mauryas , pgs 17,40,185 new persian :   takht - e jamshid or   pārseh ) , literally meaning " city of persians " , was the ceremonial capital of the achaemenid empire ( ) .

ancient civilizations : while conquering this ancient empire , alexander the great burned the buildings of persepolis , its capitol

